jodd.db.oom

Class DbOomQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • jodd.db.DbQuery<DbOomQuery>
      • jodd.db.oom.DbOomQuery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class DbOomQuery
extends DbQuery<DbOomQuery>
    A simple ORM extension for DbQuery.

    OOM extension may map results to objects in two ways:

    • auto mode - when result set is mapped to provided types, and
    • mapped mode - requires explicit mapping definitions.

      • setFetchSize

        public Q setFetchSize(int rows)
        Gives the JDBC driver a hint as to the number of rows that should be fetched from the database when more rows are needed. The number of rows specified affects only result sets created using this statement. If the value specified is zero, then the hint is ignored. The default value is zero.

      • executeCount

        public long executeCount()
        Special execute() for 'select count(*)' queries. Query is not closed after the execution unless auto-close mode is set. Doesn't check if query is really a count query, so it would work for any query that has number in the first column of result. If result set returns zero rows (very unlikely), returns -1.
